{
  "text": "The results of our studies suggest that dysfunction of RPE as measured by EOG is present in patients with NF-1. Enlargement of the analysed eyes of patients with NF-1 (from 35 to 67 eyes) did not change significantly the EOG results obtained in a group of patients with NF-1 published previously [CITATION_1] . We observed a supernormal EOG (increased AIs) in 58% of analyzed eyes in individuals with NF-1. Subnormal EOG was not found in this group of patients. Detection of changes by EOG and in parallel small changes in ERG what was shown previously [CITATION_2] indicating that the occurrence of abnormalities was mainly in the RPE.",
  "citation_candidates": [
